Clause Text:
Delivery of Assets By The Client

The Parties recognize that time is of the essence in this agreement. Specifically, {customer_identifier} recognizes that {service_provider_designation} has reserved time to perform the Services and that {service_provider_designation} will be required to turn down other projects as a result of this Agreement. As such, the parties agree to the following schedule to ensure that work can commence quickly to minimize the loss of potential revenue from other projects to {service_provider_designation}.

Within {asset_list_deadline} days of the effective date of this agreement, {service_provider_designation} shall provide {customer_identifier} with a list of all assets required to begin work on the Service (the “Required Assets List”). {service_provider_designation} shall not begin work on the Services until {customer_identifier} provides all items identified in the Required Assets List. {customer_identifier} shall provide those assets to {service_provider_designation} within {asset_deadline} days of receiving the Required Assets List.

In the event {customer_identifier} fails to provide the assets as required herein, {service_provider_designation} shall be allowed to take on additional projects and prioritize those projects over the delivery of Services to {customer_identifier} as set forth in this Agreement. In the event that {service_provider_designation} takes on an additional project as a result of {customer_identifier}’s failure to deliver the items on the Required Assets List in the timeline set forth above, {customer_identifier}'s project shall be delayed, and {customer_identifier} shall not be entitled to a refund of any fees paid.
Clause Help: This section sets out a timeline for your client to deliver all the assets you'll need to perform the services in this agreement. The goal of the clause is to ensure that you don't have to turn down other work while your client fails to deliver the assets you need in a timely fashion.
Delete Warning: If you will have to turn down other work to take on this project and your client's delay in providing assets could set you back, you should include this clause. Without it, you will be stuck waiting for your client to deliver the assets.

Clause Text:
Term & Termination

This Agreement shall commence as of the Effective Date and shall continue thereafter until the completion of the Services unless sooner terminated for cause as set forth herein.

Either Party may terminate this Agreement for cause, effective upon written notice to the other Party (the “Defaulting Party”), if the Defaulting Party:

  • materially breaches this Agreement, and such breach is incapable of cure, or with respect to a material breach capable of cure, the Defaulting Party does not cure such breach within 15 days after receipt of written notice of such breach;
  • becomes insolvent or admits its inability to pay its debts generally as they become due;
  • becomes subject, voluntarily or involuntarily, to any proceeding under any domestic or foreign bankruptcy or insolvency law, which is not fully stayed within seven business days or is not dismissed or vacated within 45 business days after filing;
  • is dissolved or liquidated or takes any corporate action for such purpose;
  • makes a general assignment for the benefit of creditors; or
  • has a receiver, trustee, custodian, or similar agent appointed by order of any court of competent jurisdiction to take charge of or sell any material portion of its property or business.


{service_provider_designation} may terminate this Agreement for cause before the expiration date of the Term on written notice if {customer_identifier} fails to pay any amount when due hereunder and such failure continues for 15 days after {customer_identifier}'s receipt of written notice of nonpayment.
Clause Help: This section provides that either party can end the agreement if the other party declares bankruptcy or takes other actions that are on the way to bankruptcy. It's meant as an out if the other party is not going to be able to live up to their side of the bargain.
Delete Warning: This is a pretty standard clause that you generally want to include in an agreement. If you remove this clause, you might have to perform the services for your client even if it is pretty clear they will not be able to pay you (or any payments they have made to you might be clawed back).

Clause Text:
Termination And Access Restriction

The Company reserves the right, in its sole discretion, to terminate Your access to the Program and the related services or any portion thereof at any time, if You become disruptive to the Company or other Program participants, if You fail to follow the Program guidelines, or if You otherwise violate this Agreement. You shall not be entitled to a refund of any portion of the fees and shall not be excused from any remaining payments under a payment plan in the event of such termination.
Clause Help: This section says that if a customer causes trouble or violates the agreement, you have the right to kick them out of the Program without having to give them a refund.
Delete Warning: This type of clause is a must for a group program. Without it, you would not have express permission to remove even the most unruly participant from your program. You should not remove it unless you have a compelling reason to do so.

Clause Text:
Cancellation Policy

The Program is offered on an ongoing basis with an auto-renewing subscription. You may cancel subscriptions at any time by following the instructions inside the membership portal or emailing {cancellation_email_address}. You will retain access to the elements of the Program, which are set forth below, until the end of the existing subscription period. Upon the completion of the existing subscription period, You will lose access to all aspects of the Program unless otherwise noted below. You shall not be charged after a cancellation.
Clause Help: This section explains how members may cancel and that they will keep access to the membership until the end of the period they have already paid for.
Delete Warning: You are legally required to have a clearly stated cancellation policy. Do not remove this clause.

Clause Text:

Clause Text:
Access To Relevant Technology

To the extent that is necessary for the {service_provider_designation} to complete the work set out in the Statement of Work, the {customer_identifier} shall provide access to all the necessary systems, accounts, and other protected assets required in order to complete the work. The {customer_identifier} shall provide secure access to these accounts via {mode_of_access}.
Clause Help: This clause explains how the client will provide access to the tools that are part of the clients tech stack so the service provider can complete the work.

Clause Text:
{customer_identifier}'s Obligations

{customer_identifier} understands that {service_provider_designation} cannot perform the services under this Agreement effectively without receiving certain information from {customer_identifier}. To facilitate the performance of the Services, {customer_identifier} shall: (1) complete any questionnaires provided to {customer_identifier} promptly, (2) provide any available market research, testimonials, and other material related to the service, (3) be available to {service_provider_designation} to collaborate with and answer questions for the {service_provider_designation}. Failure to meet these obligations shall constitute a material breach of the agreement.
Clause Help: This clause sets out the client's obligations to assist the copywriter by providing information and being available to answer questions.
Delete Warning: You generally will not be able to perform your copywriting services if the client does not provide certain information for your use, which means you need to have a section of the agreement that sets out how your client will provide that information. Removing this clause creates risk for you because it can create confusion about what your client needs to do to facilitate the work.

Clause Text:
No Rescheduling

{customer_identifier} acknowledges that {service_provider_designation} has reserved the date of the Session for {customer_identifier}'s use and that {service_provider_designation} cannot take on other work to be performed on that date. As such, {customer_identifier} agrees that the Session may not be rescheduled. {service_provider_designation} shall be entitled to retain the fees even if {customer_identifier} does not attend the session.
Clause Help: This clause sets out that the client may not reschedule the session called for by this agreement and that the copywriter is entitled to retain the fees paid under this agreement even if the client does not show up for the session.
Delete Warning: You should not remove this clause. You indicated that clients are not allowed to reschedule. When you have a policy against rescheduling, it should be included in your agreement so there is no confusion by your client.

Clause Text:
Rescheduling The Session

{customer_identifier} acknowledges that {service_provider_designation} has reserved the date of the Session for {customer_identifier}'s use and that {service_provider_designation} cannot take on other work to be performed on that date. As such, {customer_identifier} recognizes that any rescheduling must be arranged in advance or {customer_identifier} shall forfeit the fee paid under this agreement. Specifically, {customer_identifier} may not cancel or reschedule the Session with less than {rescheduling_deadline}-days’ notice. {service_provider_designation} will not be required to reschedule any session with less that {rescheduling_deadline}-days’ notice. Any cancellation made with less than {rescheduling_deadline}-days’ notice shall result in forfeiture of the Session and the payment made pursuant to this Agreement.
Clause Help: This clause sets out the deadline for the client to reschedule the day rate session. Because the copywriter is holding the day open and cannot take on other work to be performed that day, this section sets a deadline for any rescheduling. If the client does not reschedule before that deadline, the copywriter will retain the fee regardless of whether the client uses the day rate session.
Delete Warning: You should not remove this clause. Without a rescheduling clause, your client might try to reschedule at the last minute, leaving you without recourse. You can always decide to show grace and allow for rescheduling in extreme circumstances, but removing this clause would create uncertainty about whether you can hold clients to the dates.

Either Party may terminate this Agreement for cause, effective upon written notice to the other Party (the “Defaulting Party”), if the Defaulting Party:

Clause Text:
Procedure and Scheduling

Coach and Client will agree to a mutually agreeable time for the coaching sessions. Once a coaching session is scheduled, You may not cancel or reschedule that session unless You do so at least {rescheduling_deadline} before it is scheduled to begin. Coach reserves the right to treat any meeting that Client misses or attempts to reschedule less than {rescheduling_deadline} before it is scheduled to begin as having been used by Client.
Clause Help: This clause sets out how the coaching sessions are scheduled and sets out the deadline for Client to ask to reschedule those calls.
Delete Warning: If you do not include a clause that includes deadlines for a client to reschedule, you run the risk that your clients will repeatedly reschedule at the last minute.

Clause Text:
Use of Public Comments And Praise

To preserve the Client’s confidences, the Coach will not publicly post anything about Client’s sessions or coaching experience on social media or otherwise without the Client’s express written permission.

To the extent Client chooses to make any public disclosures about the coaching experience, whether through social media or other media, the Coach may reshare that information. This will include the right to reshare the Client’s comments, praise, or other disclosure on social media and other online platforms. In other words, if You choose to say anything about the coaching experience publicly, the Coach has the right to use those public comments to market and promote the Coach’s business.

This will include any necessary licenses to the copyright in Your post and the right to use Your name, image, or likeness (to the extent they are attached to Your post) to promote the Coach’s business.
Clause Help: This clause explains that the coach generally will not share anything about sessions with the client, but it allows the Coach to reshare anything that the client says publicly. This clause is meant to strike a delicate balance between the confidentiality inherent in a coaching relationship with the coach's desire to cheer on a client's public wins.
Delete Warning: Without this clause, there is some question about what you can share about your clients. We added this clause after feedback from multiple coaches, and we phrased it in a way that strikes a balance. Removing it will create some uncertainty.

Clause Text:
Termination

This Agreement shall continue until terminated by one of the Parties. Either Party may terminate the Agreement without cause by providing written notice prior to any ongoing monthly fee payment deadline. In the event of termination under this provision, the Coach shall continue to provide service through the end of the period for which the fees have been paid.
Clause Help: This clause sets out how either party can end the ongoing monthly coaching relationship. Under this clause, either party can end the relationship by giving notice before the next monthly payment is made.
Delete Warning: Any ongoing relationship needs to have a "termination" clause that explains how it can end. This clause sets out the standard mechanism. You should not remove this clause unless you replace it with another termination clause.

Clause Text:
Application & Acceptance

To participate in the Affiliate Program, You may be required to complete an Affiliate Program application (“Application”). You are required to answer all questions in that Application, and Your answers must be accurate and complete.

To participate in the Affiliate Program, You must provide the Company with Your true identity and other contact information, as well as business and banking information as requested. You may not use any alias, pseudonym, persona, pen name, DBA, or other means to mask Your identity or business details.

The Company will rely upon the information provided in Your Application, and any false information will be sufficient basis to reject Your Application or to terminate Your status as an Affiliate without compensation if discovered after You are approved.

The Company will review Your Application and decide whether to accept You as an Affiliate. We will notify You in due course of Your acceptance or rejection as an Affiliate. We may accept or reject Your Application at our sole discretion for any or no reason.

Upon acceptance into the Affiliate Program, You will receive an email notifying You of Your acceptance and that includes Your Affiliate credentials (including details about how to obtain Your links to share and other important information).
Clause Help: This clause sets out that people wishing to be affiliates must apply and that the Company has the right to accept or reject the application. It also provides that the potential affiliate must provide truthful information and may not use an anonymous identity to apply.
Delete Warning: Because you allow people to apply to be an affiliate, you should have a provision making clear that you have the right to reject those applications. Do not remove htis provision.

Clause Text:
Acceptable And Non-Acceptable Marketing Practices

Affiliate shall post and make available to all end-users an appropriate privacy policy that complies with all applicable federal, state, and local laws and requirements. The privacy policy shall be made available to users prior to the collection of any personally identifiable information, and shall clearly disclose all information collection, use, and sharing practices, including any collection of information in connection with the Affiliate Program.

Affiliate shall not promote Company’s products: (1) in conjunction with any illegal activity, (2) on any illegal website, (3) in a manner that a reasonable person would consider threatening, harmful, defamatory, obscene, sexually explicit, harassing, or promoting violence; (4) in a manner that promotes discrimination, (5) in any manner the Company expressly deems as objectionable, or (6) in a manner that infringes upon the intellectual property or related rights held by any third party.

Affiliate shall not make any claims, guarantees, representations, or warranties about the Company’s products, except as expressly authorized herein or in the Company’s Website Terms of Use.
Clause Help: This clause sets out basic standards for how and where your affiliates will promote your products. It ensures that your product is not associated with illegal or unethical practices.
Delete Warning: Do not delete this clause. If you need to make modifications to the list of unacceptable practices, edit the list instead.

Clause Text:
Term and Termination

This Agreement shall commence upon the date the Company notifies You that You have been accepted into the Affiliate Program and shall continue thereafter until terminated as provided herein.

The Company may terminate this Agreement in full or in part at any time and for any reason it deems appropriate with or without prior notice to You. In the event of termination, the Company will disable any tracking URLs, links, cookies, pixels, and similar mechanisms for use with the Affiliate Program. You may terminate this Agreement at any time upon notification to the Company in writing.

Upon termination, You shall immediately cease all use of the Promotional Materials and all of the Company’s intellectual property and will delete all copies of such materials in Your possession. Furthermore, You shall immediately cease representing Yourself as a participant in the Affiliate Program.

You shall be entitled to all validly accrued Commissions that have been earned prior to the termination of this Agreement.
Clause Help: This clause explains that you may terminate the affiliate program or terminate an individual affiliate, but that all commissions earned to that point will still be payable.
Delete Warning: Do not delete this clause. Without this clause, there would be uncertainty about whether you could ever terminate the affiliate program.

Clause Text:
Accessing The Website And Account Security

We reserve the right to withdraw or amend this Website and any service or material we provide on the Website in our sole discretion without notice. We will not be liable if for any reason all or any part of the Website is unavailable at any time or for any period. From time to time, we may restrict access to some parts of the Website, or the entire Website, to users, including registered users.

To access the Website or some of the resources it offers, You may be asked to provide certain registration details or other information. It is a condition of Your use of the Website and any resources downloaded from the Website that all the information You provide on the Website is correct, current, and complete. You agree that all information You provide to register with this Website or otherwise, including but not limited to through the use of any interactive features on the Website, is governed by our Privacy Policy, and You consent to all actions we take with respect to Your information consistent with our Privacy Policy.

If You choose or receive a username, password, or any other piece of information as part of our security procedures, You must treat such information as confidential, and You must not disclose it to any other person or entity. You also acknowledge that Your account is personal to You and agree not to provide any other person with access to this Website or portions of it using Your username, password, or other security information. You agree to notify us immediately of any unauthorized access to or use of Your user name or password or any other breach of security. You also agree to ensure that You exit from Your account at the end of each session. You should use particular caution when accessing Your account from a public or shared computer so that others are not able to view or record Your password or other personal information.

We have the right to disable any user name, password, or other identifier, whether chosen by You or provided by us, at any time in our sole discretion for any or no reason, including if, in our opinion, You have violated any provision of these Terms of Use.
Clause Help: This clause does a couple of things. First, it sets out that you may take the website down at any time. Second, it explains that you may require information to access the website (or other resources) and requires users to protect usernames, passwords, etc.
Delete Warning: You generally should include this clause. If you do not use usernames or passwords and are confident you never will, you can remove the final two paragraphs to simplify.
Plain Text Name: Accessing The Website And Account Security

Clause Text:
Editorial Standards & Discretion

Your submission of the Guest Post for consideration does not guarantee that it will be published. The Company is selective on what it publishes on its blog and reserves the right to reject Your Guest Post submission for any reason.

The Company only publishes original works that have not been published elsewhere and that have not been submitted for publication elsewhere. As such, as a condition of submitting Your Guest Post for consideration, You represent and warrant: (1) that the Guest Post is an original work that You authored, (2) that the Guest Post has not been published elsewhere, and (3) that the Guest Post is not currently under consideration for publication by any other parties.
Clause Help: This clause makes clear that your company has absolute discretion in deciding whether to accept the guest post and requires that the post be original and not published anywhere else.
Delete Warning: Do not remove this clause unless you want to allow people to submit posts that they have already published elsewhere.

Clause Text:
Submission Process

You represent and warrant that You are currently the sole owner of all intellectual property rights to the Guest Post and that the publication of the Guest Post by the Company will not infringe on any copyrights or other intellectual property rights of any person, firm, corporation, or other entity.

You further agree to give the Company a period of no less than {guest_post_consideration_period} days to consider Your Guest Post before submitting it for consideration by any other publication. If the Company does not notify You that Your Guest Post has been selected for publication within {guest_post_consideration_period} days of submission, You are free to submit it for publication elsewhere.
Clause Help: This clause requires the guest blogger to assure you that they own the material they are submitting and it gives you a designated period to decide whether to accept the post.
Delete Warning: Do not remove this clause. The first paragraph is important because it includes the necessary assurances that the guest blogger actually has the right to submit the work. Without the second paragraph, the author might submit the work elsewhere, which could create copyright issues down the line.

Clause Text:
Publication Process

If Your Guest Post is selected for publication, the Company shall credit You as the author of the Guest Post on the page on which it is published. Further, the Guest Post will include a biographical section about You, and that section will include a link to Your website.

You expressly agree that You will not receive any monetary compensation for the inclusion of the Guest Post on the Blog. Instead, You agree that the intangible value in exposure You obtain through publication is sufficient consideration for the rights You are granting under this Agreement.

You further agree to allow the Company the right to edit and adapt Your Guest Post to correct grammatical errors and increase clarity. You also agree that the Company may add calls to action to the Company’s other content and to add links to related content.
Clause Help: This clause explains that you'll include biographical information about the author and a link to the author's website. It also makes clear the author will not be paid and that your company can edit the post.
Delete Warning: Do not delete this clause. Removing this section would leave uncertainty about whether the author will be paid and whether you can edit posts.
